This has been a wild coverup project. Some is fresh, most is healed.  90% of this was done by another artist. I used a couple of new flowers to cover up old stuff at the top, and then we blacked out the rest! 
The process has been a lesson for sure and a big reminder to clients: never feel like your artist’s ego is worth more than your happiness!! It’s your body, get the tattoos you want ❤️❤️❤️
SNAKE!!! So much fun :)

For those who don’t know, I book my appointments 3-4 months at a time. I’m currently compiling my list of requests for March - June sessions and will be building my schedule soon. If you’d like to get into the mix send me an email requesting a consultation form. Get it filled out and back to me asap to be on the Spring 2023 list! emily@emilyshoichet.com 
 Thanks friends!

This is phase 3 of a wonderfully challenging project. Phase 1 & 2 were blacking out the upper arm covering an old tribal piece. Phase 3 white & black lines. We’re going to have to do multiple passes of the white to build it up. And I’m going to go over the black again to even it out. Props to anyone who can do big fields of solid black in one go. “The kid wants to hear the story again, Grizz.”
“Again?” huffs the old wizard, feigning irritation. “Very well then!” 
 The old barbarian winks his one good eye at the child. They both know how much Grizz loves to tell tales of the old days, and the barbarian knows how much the child loves to hear them.
 “There we were face to face with the giant beast!! It’s eye glowed a terrible red!! We were cornered! never gonna make it out alive! Crumpch readied his axe, and I had one last spell ready to go….”
